@flan This is how I had done it,

1) Create a JSON ruleset something like below, API (/rulename/definition)
`
rulename$state: {
cond1: {
all: {
$m: {
$gt: {
amount: 0
}
}
},
run: "valid",
to: "valid"
}
},
valid: {}
`
2) Then if you pass {amount:100,sId:1} to this, it will change its state to valid. (API: /rulename/event)
3) To get the current state you have call another api (/rulename/events/1). This will return a JSON which you can evaluate current state as valid. So based on this state you can call you server side function. So if you want additional data then you can pass it along with the request in step 2.



This is based on my understanding. @jruizgit might have a better understanding.

